This section provides links to other security-related services available for Ops Manager deployments.

For information about other security-related tiles provided by Pivotal partners, see [Pivotal Network](https://network.pivotal.io/) and the [Pivotal documentation](https://docs.pivotal.io).


## <a id="tiles"></a> Tiles

This section provides links to security-related tiles available for Ops Manager deployments.

* [Single Sign-On (SSO)](https://docs.pivotal.io/p-identity/index.html): Provides support for native authentication, federated single sign-on, and authorization.

* [CredHub Service Broker](https://docs.pivotal.io/credhub-service-broker/index.html): Allows apps running on Pivotal Application Service (PAS) to access secure credentials in CredHub.

* [Compliance Scanner](https://docs.pivotal.io/addon-compliance-tools/index.html): Enables operators and auditors to conduct compliance scanning of BOSH-managed Xenial VMs against configuration hardening guidelines.


## <a id="add-ons"></a> Add-ons

This section provides links to security-related BOSH add-ons available for Ops Manager deployments.

* [File Integrity Monitoring](https://docs.pivotal.io/addon-fim/index.html): Provides File Integrity Monitoring (FIM) protection within the Ops Manager environment. This monitoring is sometimes required for compliance purposes.

* [IPsec for VMware Tanzu](https://docs.pivotal.io/addon-ipsec/index.html): Adds security to the network layer for each BOSH-deployed virtual machine (VM), increasing internal protection if a malicious actor breaches your firewall.
  * [Securing Data in Transit with the IPsec Add-on](http://docs.pivotal.io/addon-ipsec/)
  * [Rotating IPsec Credentials](http://docs.pivotal.io/addon-ipsec/credentials.html)
  * [Installing IPsec](http://docs.pivotal.io/addon-ipsec/installing.html)

* [Anti-Virus](https://docs.pivotal.io/addon-antivirus/index.html): Provides antivirus protection within the Ops Manager environment. This protection is sometimes required for compliance purposes.
